cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.LO, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the extension of the quotient operation to formal power series and its implications in the study of weighted automata, which are fundamental topics in formal languages and automata theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the construction of minimal deterministic finite automata and universal automata, which are important data structures in automata theory and computer science.
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is another possible category as the paper deals with algebraic properties of formal power series and their operations, which are related to symbolic computation and manipulation of mathematical expressions.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with closure properties of regular series and weighted context-free series, which are related to logic and formal reasoning.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of constructing the universal automaton and the minimization of deterministic weighted automata, which are related to computational complexity and algorithmic efficiency.
